                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-defend1429" type="age" value="25"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18280410-259-off1388" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-off1388" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-off1388" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280410-259-cd1389" type="crimeDate">22d of March</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-259-off1388 t18280410-259-cd1389"></join>, 11 books, value 36s.; and one quilt, value 8s.
            </rs>; the goods of 
               <persName id="t18280410-259-victim1430" type="victimName">
                  John Jones 
                  Price
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-victim1430" type="surname" value="Price"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-victim1430" type="given" value="John Jones"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-victim1430" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-259-off1388 t18280410-259-victim1430"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-259-person1431">
                  CHARLES 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1431" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1431" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1431" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Mr. Price, a <rs id="t18280410-259-viclabel1390" type="occupation">pawnbroker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280410-259-victim1430 t18280410-259-viclabel1390"></join> of Wentworth-street. On the night of the 22d of March, about a quarter before eleven o'clock, I observed our inside window open; I was behind the counter opposite to it - I saw the prisoner with the window in one hand, and a bed quilt in the other, tied up in a handkerchief, which had been in the window; I gave an alarm - he went to the door and tried to escape; the shop was full of people - I went out and seized him; he dropped the quilt on his left side, the moment he got out at the door.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-259-person1432">
                  SUSANNAH 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1432" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1432" type="given" value="SUSANNAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1432" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at Mr. Price's; I saw Brown jump over the counter, and go to the door; he took hold of the prisoner, and I took hold of him - I saw him drop the quilt and several books at the same time.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-259-person1433">
                  JOHN 
                  POWELL
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1433" type="surname" value="POWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1433" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1433" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman; I took the prisoner down to the watch-house - I searched him, and found a pair of shoes on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-259-person1434">
                  JOHN 
                  DUNGATE
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1434" type="surname" value="DUNGATE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1434" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1434" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I produce the property which was brought to the watch-house with the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280410-259-person1435">
                  JOHN 
                  JONES PRICE
               <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1435" type="surname" value="JONES PRICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1435" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-person1435" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep this shop; I was at home, and heard a bustle - I told Brown to jump over the counter, and see what was the matter, which he did; these articles are my property - they were brought in by different people out of the street; he came in by the door, and there are folding doors to the window, fastened with a button, eight feet high - I should not have thought a person could have reached it.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to pawn a pair of shoes that night; they accused me of having the property - but there was none on me, it was out at the door.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280410-259-verdict1391" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280410-259-verdict1391" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>
